23
00:04:11.181 --> 00:04:12.307
How did you find me?

24
00:05:33.305 --> 00:05:34.306
Don't…

25
00:05:35.390 --> 00:05:37.517
Don't go back!

26
00:05:48.069 --> 00:05:48.945
Ruja.

27
00:05:51.323 --> 00:05:52.449
We're here.

28
00:05:52.907 --> 00:05:54.075
Let's get inside.

29
00:05:57.871 --> 00:06:02.250
CHIANG MAI

30
00:06:33.907 --> 00:06:36.368
Grandma's house is so big.

31
00:07:15.532 --> 00:07:18.243
What's this room, mommy?

32
00:07:18.868 --> 00:07:20.036
Dining room, honey.

33
00:09:23.868 --> 00:09:24.828
Let's go.

34
00:09:28.498 --> 00:09:32.001
Mommy, are we moving here?

35
00:09:34.754 --> 00:09:35.713
No.

36
00:09:37.257 --> 00:09:39.717
We're here just for a few days.

37
00:09:47.350 --> 00:09:48.560
Hi, Da.

38
00:09:49.102 --> 00:09:51.688
Welcome home, ma'am.

39
00:09:57.527 --> 00:10:00.446
This is Rachel, my daughter.

40
00:10:00.530 --> 00:10:01.739
Ruja.

41
00:10:02.490 --> 00:10:04.492
Come to the studio with me.

42
00:10:05.869 --> 00:10:07.787
Da can look after Rachel.

43
00:10:09.372 --> 00:10:10.665
Now?

44
00:10:10.748 --> 00:10:12.959
Yes. I'll have to leave soon.

45
00:10:13.376 --> 00:10:14.752
It won't take long.

46
00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:25.930
Can you stay with Da? 
I'll be right back.

47
00:10:26.014 --> 00:10:28.391
But I want to come with you.

48
00:10:29.392 --> 00:10:32.145
Kids are not allowed
in the studio, Rachel.


49
00:10:32.228 --> 00:10:34.856
Stay here with me.

50
00:10:35.481 --> 00:10:38.943
I'll show you your bedroom upstairs.
Want to see it?


51
00:10:44.407 --> 00:10:45.450
Come on.

52
00:10:46.075 --> 00:10:46.993
Wait.

53
00:10:47.911 --> 00:10:50.205
Rachel has eye problems.

54
00:10:50.914 --> 00:10:52.457
Please be very careful.

55
00:10:53.416 --> 00:10:54.667
Yes, ma'am.

56
00:10:55.793 --> 00:10:57.003
Let's go.

57
00:11:31.955 --> 00:11:32.830
Ruja.

58
00:11:45.176 --> 00:11:46.219
Come in.

59
00:12:19.669 --> 00:12:23.798
Look here, Portrait of a Beauty,
Number One and Number Two.


60
00:12:37.228 --> 00:12:40.690
Your father painted them
over 20 years ago.


61
00:12:41.691 --> 00:12:45.737
Painting Number One
was sold to one of his fans for…


62
00:12:46.988 --> 00:12:48.322
several million.

63
00:12:50.158 --> 00:12:52.827
But it was returned to this studio…

64
00:12:57.248 --> 00:12:58.458
because…

65
00:13:02.670 --> 00:13:08.092
<i>the owner killed all his family members</i>
<i>and then killed himself.</i>


66
00:13:08.926 --> 00:13:10.970
<i>He left a note under the painting.</i>

67
00:13:11.429 --> 00:13:12.680
<i>It said…</i>

68
00:13:13.222 --> 00:13:16.934
<i>''I'm returning you to your creator.''</i>

69
00:13:19.103 --> 00:13:22.023
So, we got it back for free.

70
00:13:25.359 --> 00:13:28.488
As for Number Two,
Pakorn kept it in good condition.


71
00:13:28.571 --> 00:13:30.073
Said it wasn't for sale.

72
00:13:30.656 --> 00:13:31.783
But now,

73
00:13:32.784 --> 00:13:36.412
a millionaire is willing to pay a fortune

74
00:13:36.496 --> 00:13:38.206
to buy both of them.

75
00:13:38.706 --> 00:13:40.875
I need your permission first.

76
00:13:40.958 --> 00:13:42.335
When will we get the money?

77
00:13:49.717 --> 00:13:54.680
Are you not even going to ask
how your father died?


78
00:14:02.855 --> 00:14:04.982
Yummy, Rachel?

79
00:14:05.358 --> 00:14:06.484
Yummy.

80
00:14:08.277 --> 00:14:11.447
Let me ask you something.

81
00:14:12.865 --> 00:14:14.617
How's your grandma Vipa doing?

82
00:14:15.159 --> 00:14:17.286
Grandma died, from cancer.

83
00:14:19.747 --> 00:14:20.873
Did she?

84
00:14:22.792 --> 00:14:24.752
She didn't hang herself?

85
00:14:26.421 --> 00:14:27.964
Pakorn, your father…

86
00:14:30.258 --> 00:14:32.718
hung himself here.

87
00:14:34.887 --> 00:14:36.431
From that beam.

88
00:14:44.230 --> 00:14:46.774
What is "hang herself?"

89
00:14:49.944 --> 00:14:52.363
Never mind. Forget it.

90
00:14:54.532 --> 00:14:56.576
Forgive him, Ruja.

91
00:14:57.326 --> 00:15:01.247
Think of these expensive paintings

92
00:15:01.330 --> 00:15:03.416
as his redemption.

93
00:15:04.459 --> 00:15:06.002
Are we done?

94
00:15:07.086 --> 00:15:08.838
I want to get out of here.

95
00:15:35.615 --> 00:15:37.241
Rachel, where're you going?

96
00:15:37.325 --> 00:15:38.784
I want to see mommy.

97
00:15:43.331 --> 00:15:45.166
Where did you get that?

98
00:15:46.626 --> 00:15:49.462
You gave it to me just now.

99
00:15:56.677 --> 00:15:58.429
Let me have it back.

100
00:15:59.639 --> 00:16:01.307
I'll wash it for you first.

101
00:16:03.768 --> 00:16:06.896
You wait for your mommy here.
She'll be back soon.


102
00:16:06.979 --> 00:16:08.189
<i>One more thing.</i>

103
00:16:08.856 --> 00:16:10.942
The paintings have some cracks.

104
00:16:11.859 --> 00:16:15.905
I want them fixed before we sell them.

105
00:16:17.281 --> 00:16:20.743
My son is an art restorer,
he can take care of it.


106
00:16:20.826 --> 00:16:23.287
If you think it's necessary, do it.

107
00:16:25.831 --> 00:16:26.916
One more thing…

108
00:16:29.377 --> 00:16:31.087
After his funeral,

109
00:16:32.964 --> 00:16:34.715
I want to sell this house too.

110
00:16:35.675 --> 00:16:37.552
Please see to it for me.

111
00:17:34.692 --> 00:17:35.735
Mommy?

112
00:18:08.017 --> 00:18:09.018
Rachel!

113
00:18:12.229 --> 00:18:13.731
What are you doing?

114
00:19:39.525 --> 00:19:41.610
Please don't hold it against me!

115
00:20:17.688 --> 00:20:19.023
Mommy…

116
00:20:21.150 --> 00:20:25.362
Grandpa's paintings. 
Why can't I see them?

117
00:20:26.280 --> 00:20:28.157
They're scary.

118
00:20:28.240 --> 00:20:29.784
How scary?

119
00:20:30.993 --> 00:20:35.748
So scary that you'll have nightmares.

120
00:20:36.373 --> 00:20:38.417
You don't like nightmares, do you?

121
00:20:41.837 --> 00:20:43.964
Aren't you scared, mommy?

122
00:20:52.973 --> 00:20:56.685
Why does dad paint you like that?

123
00:20:57.394 --> 00:20:59.855
It's just an act.

124
00:21:00.773 --> 00:21:02.566
Like in a play.

125
00:21:03.442 --> 00:21:06.403
It helped dad create nice paintings.

126
00:21:08.989 --> 00:21:11.158
But you cried.

127
00:21:15.371 --> 00:21:16.956
It's nothing, Ruja.

128
00:21:18.874 --> 00:21:22.628
But you must not go
into dad's studio again.


129
00:21:23.045 --> 00:21:25.381
He needs to focus on his work.

130
00:21:26.006 --> 00:21:28.008
Promise me, dear.

131
00:22:02.626 --> 00:22:05.129
I miss your grandma, honey.

132
00:22:20.269 --> 00:22:22.062
Don't cry, mommy.

133
00:22:24.815 --> 00:22:26.275
Don't cry.

