176
00:28:50.617 --> 00:28:53.203
Where were you? 
You scared me to death.

177
00:28:53.287 --> 00:28:56.873
I took a walk and I met him.

178
00:28:57.666 --> 00:28:59.042
Are you Ruja?

179
00:28:59.126 --> 00:29:00.377
My name's Tim.

180
00:29:00.460 --> 00:29:03.297
I'm here to fix the paintings,
my dad must have told you.


181
00:29:07.843 --> 00:29:09.803
Where did you go for a walk?

182
00:29:13.890 --> 00:29:15.434
Tell me where.

183
00:29:16.268 --> 00:29:17.853
By the stream back there.

184
00:29:20.939 --> 00:29:23.817
It's dangerous.

185
00:29:24.651 --> 00:29:26.570
Don't do it again.

186
00:29:26.945 --> 00:29:29.531
What would I do
if something happened to you?


187
00:29:29.614 --> 00:29:31.158
I wasn't alone.

188
00:29:31.742 --> 00:29:34.870
I went with the
woman with a red scarf.

189
00:29:34.953 --> 00:29:35.954
Stop lying.

190
00:29:36.621 --> 00:29:37.998
I'm not lying.

191
00:29:38.081 --> 00:29:39.041
Rachel.

192
00:29:47.674 --> 00:29:49.051
I'm sorry.

193
00:29:51.261 --> 00:29:53.555
Please don't do it again.

194
00:29:56.892 --> 00:29:58.769
I'm sorry, honey.

195
00:30:18.747 --> 00:30:19.706
Here.

196
00:30:19.790 --> 00:30:20.665
Thank you.

197
00:30:25.545 --> 00:30:26.546
Da,

198
00:30:27.297 --> 00:30:29.466
what happened to your ankle?

199
00:30:29.549 --> 00:30:33.553
Just a sprain. 
Nothing serious.

200
00:30:41.186 --> 00:30:42.145
Excuse me.

201
00:30:42.854 --> 00:30:45.023
What were you doing in the woods?

202
00:30:45.107 --> 00:30:46.942
I paint landscapes.

203
00:30:47.442 --> 00:30:51.154
My dad said there's a beautiful stream
behind the house.


204
00:30:51.822 --> 00:30:53.115
So I went to look.

205
00:30:53.198 --> 00:30:56.284
And luckily, I bumped into Rachel.

206
00:30:56.368 --> 00:30:58.537
Rachel has eye problems.

207
00:30:59.371 --> 00:31:01.123
It's not safe for her to wander around.

208
00:31:01.665 --> 00:31:02.916
I see.

209
00:31:02.999 --> 00:31:04.626
But thank you anyway.

210
00:31:06.420 --> 00:31:07.504
Look…

211
00:31:09.423 --> 00:31:10.757
I'll show you my sketches.

212
00:31:12.926 --> 00:31:14.761
Even better, I'll draw you.

213
00:31:20.809 --> 00:31:23.145
You don't have to please her.

214
00:31:23.228 --> 00:31:25.480
It's okay. I really want to draw her.

215
00:31:25.814 --> 00:31:26.773
Here we go.

216
00:31:49.379 --> 00:31:50.213
Done.

217
00:31:52.048 --> 00:31:53.216
Want to see it?

218
00:31:58.555 --> 00:31:59.639
It's ugly.

219
00:32:02.601 --> 00:32:04.186
I think it's pretty.

220
00:32:04.853 --> 00:32:06.021
How about this?

221
00:32:07.147 --> 00:32:10.775
Next time I'll draw you
like a princess. Okay?


222
00:32:12.110 --> 00:32:13.111
I'm sorry.

223
00:32:14.112 --> 00:32:16.907
How long will it take
to fix the paintings?


224
00:32:17.699 --> 00:32:20.911
I need to see them
before I can answer that.


225
00:32:20.994 --> 00:32:25.165
But I've heard the damages
are minor. Right?


226
00:35:28.390 --> 00:35:33.228
Mommy, when will the rain stop?
I want to play outside.


227
00:35:34.979 --> 00:35:35.855
Rachel.

228
00:35:37.565 --> 00:35:39.067
Listen to mommy.

229
00:35:39.651 --> 00:35:44.614
From now on, when you want to go outside
you have to ask me first.


230
00:35:45.407 --> 00:35:46.658
Understand?

231
00:35:47.325 --> 00:35:49.786
Can I go with Tim?

232
00:35:50.495 --> 00:35:51.621
No, you can't.

233
00:35:52.038 --> 00:35:54.332
But I like him.

234
00:35:56.626 --> 00:36:00.046
I want him to draw my picture.

235
00:36:01.506 --> 00:36:02.340
Ruja.

236
00:36:02.716 --> 00:36:03.591
Tim.

237
00:36:03.925 --> 00:36:05.218
Hi, Rachel.

238
00:36:06.302 --> 00:36:07.345
How's it going?

239
00:36:09.639 --> 00:36:11.725
Let me talk to
your mommy for a second.

240
00:36:13.017 --> 00:36:15.895
You should come see
something in the studio.


241
00:36:17.856 --> 00:36:19.441
Can I come too?

242
00:36:21.151 --> 00:36:24.821
Whatever it is,
you don't need my permission.


243
00:36:24.904 --> 00:36:26.906
It's not about the restoration.

244
00:36:27.741 --> 00:36:29.909
Believe me, you have to see it.

245
00:36:40.879 --> 00:36:41.755
This.

246
00:36:45.675 --> 00:36:49.512
I had no idea it was this bad.

247
00:36:50.555 --> 00:36:51.973
Look at these cracks.

248
00:37:00.607 --> 00:37:01.900
What's the matter?

249
00:37:05.820 --> 00:37:06.780
Nothing.

250
00:37:17.457 --> 00:37:18.875
What are you doing?

251
00:37:21.044 --> 00:37:22.629
You'll ruin it even more.

252
00:37:22.712 --> 00:37:25.465
I have to fix it anyway, right?

253
00:37:50.782 --> 00:37:52.450
Put it back right now.

254
00:37:55.578 --> 00:37:58.456
Don't you want to see what's underneath?

255
00:37:58.790 --> 00:37:59.791
No.

256
00:38:01.835 --> 00:38:03.628
It could be a big discovery,

257
00:38:03.711 --> 00:38:07.423
may raise the value
of your father's paintings artistically--


258
00:38:07.507 --> 00:38:10.468
I don't care. Okay? Put it back.

259
00:38:14.347 --> 00:38:15.682
You should care.

260
00:38:16.558 --> 00:38:18.309
If you want to sell it.

261
00:38:23.898 --> 00:38:25.024
Or…

262
00:38:26.317 --> 00:38:28.736
Do you think it's haunted?

263
00:38:33.241 --> 00:38:34.409
Nonsense.

264
00:38:35.618 --> 00:38:36.703
I'm kidding.

265
00:38:40.915 --> 00:38:42.166
But I don't get it.

266
00:38:43.668 --> 00:38:47.130
People always think of ghosts
when they see unexpected things.


267
00:38:48.089 --> 00:38:49.799
But everything can be explained.

268
00:38:51.593 --> 00:38:52.510
Listen…

269
00:38:53.303 --> 00:38:54.929
You know the Mona Lisa?

270
00:38:58.391 --> 00:38:59.559
You do.

271
00:39:00.351 --> 00:39:04.939
They say when you
lock your eyes with hers

272
00:39:05.356 --> 00:39:09.944
her gaze will follow you
no matter where you walk in the room.


273
00:39:10.028 --> 00:39:12.196
But it has nothing to do with ghosts.

274
00:39:12.614 --> 00:39:14.449
The same with this painting.

275
00:39:15.366 --> 00:39:16.451
Let's test it.

276
00:39:35.178 --> 00:39:37.889
See for yourself
so you'll stop being afraid.


277
00:39:43.269 --> 00:39:44.270
Let's try.

278
00:39:44.979 --> 00:39:46.648
Look her in the eyes.

279
00:39:49.233 --> 00:39:50.818
And walk this way.

280
00:40:15.718 --> 00:40:17.470
Is she following you?

281
00:40:19.847 --> 00:40:21.599
See? I told you.

282
00:40:41.744 --> 00:40:42.745
What's wrong?

283
00:40:46.290 --> 00:40:48.584
Just fix the damn thing.

